    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nI studied the codebase thoroughly — particularly `packages/black-forest-labs/` as the simplest existing image-only provider — and produced a detailed step-by-step plan. Here's an overview:\n\n### What gets created (9 files in `packages/pixelart/`)\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `package.json` | `@ai-sdk/pixelart` v0.0.1, same shape as black-forest-labs |\n| `tsconfig.json` | Extends `@vercel/ai-tsconfig/ts-library.json`, refs `../provider` + `../provider-utils` |\n| `tsconfig.build.json` | Extends tsconfig.json with `composite: false` for tsup |\n| `tsup.config.ts` | Single entry `src/index.ts`, ESM+CJS output with dts |\n| `src/version.ts` | Standard `__PACKAGE_VERSION__` injection |\n| `src/pixelart-image-model.ts` | `PixelArtImageModelId` type, `PixelArtImageSettings` Zod schema/type, `PixelArtImageModel` class implementing `ImageModelV3` |\n| `src/pixelart-provider.ts` | `PixelArtProviderSettings`, `PixelArtProvider` interface (extends `ProviderV3`), `createPixelArt` factory, default `pixelArt` instance |\n| `src/index.ts` | All public exports |\n\n### One line added to existing file\n- **Root `tsconfig.json`**: Add `{ \"path\": \"packages/pixelart\" }` to project references (needed for `pnpm type-check:full`)\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **Image model** calls `POST https://api.pixelart.ai/v1/images/generate` via `postJsonToApi`, passing `prompt`, `n`, `size`, `seed`, and provider-specific `style`/`pixel_density` parsed from `providerOptions` with `parseProviderOptions`\n- **Provider** throws `NoSuchModelError` for `languageModel`/`embeddingModel` (same pattern as Black Forest Labs)\n- **Auth**: `Authorization: Bearer <key>` header, loaded from `PIXELART_API_KEY` env var",
